Trissolcus tersus

can be identified by the line of foveae along the dorsal margin of the mesopleural carina (Figures 
189
, 
192
), a character known to us so only from this species. The setation of the posteroventral metapleuron (Figure 
189
) and the presence of facial and malar striae (Figure 
193
) are also useful for its identification.
